channel.title: AHH, Something very wrong has happened to my source! *HELP*
channel.description:
I have made any new upgrades in a week, then today i open up the folder compile and then run 0 errors compiling.... but when i run it i get this, i never have editted it and yet, it gets an error....
Starting fr33sc4p3 Server on 0.0.0.0:43594 Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NumberFormatException: For input string: "/ /STABATTACK" at java.lang.NumberFormatException.forInputString(Unknown Source) at java.lang.Integer.parseInt(Unknown Source) at java.lang.Integer.parseInt(Unknown Source) at ItemHandler.loadItemList(ItemHandler.java:313) at ItemHandler.(ItemHandler.java:39) at server.main(server.java:30)
If anyone who is obviously smarter than me can help it would be nice, by the way, i tried searching for the "Error" and i could not find anything within the sort. And yes, i did search itemhandler.java and stuff... And yes, i am SMART enough to make myself a backup but i tried that already It Don't Work.

It’s probably not the .java file, its probably the .cfg file. you might of not used tabs or something like that.\

EDIT:

Oh and btw, what is that?

“/
/STABATTACK”
?? if you were trying to comment it out its

/* then */ at the end.
